    {
      "id": "1b64750c-f3ba-805a-8a7d-ef0f126fb78d",
      "type": "paragraph",
      "text": "In K-12 there are common applications of VLE’s for classroom interaction. However, the greater success, even at this age, of using a VLE is often determined byu the learner’s SRL skills. And, while clustering techniques have been used to uncover different SRL constructs, little attention is given to algorithmic bias or fairness. ",
      "raw": {
        "object": "block",
        "id": "1b64750c-f3ba-805a-8a7d-ef0f126fb78d",
        "parent": {
